The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 GfK buys 51% of Mode

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, Aug. 16: Market research company Mode Group has tied up with German giant GfK. According to the agreement signed by the two companies, GfK will acquire 51 per cent of Mode and the combined entity will be called GfK-Mode. 

 We have achieved phenomenal growth in the domestic market in a short span of time. We wish to shift gears and to this end our chosen strategy was to join hands with an international group, said Kalyanmoy Chatterjee, chief executive officer, Mode, explaining the trigger behind the tie-up. 

 Mode conducts opinion, marketing and social research and has some top Indian and multinational companies on its list of clients. 

 GfK is among the top five market research companies in the world and has 13 German subsidiaries and 130 companies in 70 countries. The groups earning for the financial year 2005 was 937.3 million euros.




